data.title: Miami University
data.text:
As America and Miami University's first co-ed professional business fraternity, Delta Sigma Pi is committed to equipping our brothers to make a greater impact in their business, civic, and personal lives by focusing on developing every brother in each of our four foundational pillars; Professionalism, Service, Fundraising, and Brotherhood. Although each of these pillars drive our activities on and off campus, our organization's strong brotherhood and professionalism allow our brothers to build unbreakable personal and professional relationships, creating a vast network of brothers you can always count on and is what sets Delta Sigma Pi apart from any other organization on campus.

Our Mission

At the Alpha Upsilon Chapter of the International Fraternity of Delta Sigma Pi, we strive for excellence in everything we do. DSP is a close-knit group of friends who always go the extra mile for each other. We are a diverse, yet cooperative and dynamic group who motivate one another to succeed in every aspect of our lives. As leaders, we strive to develop each other and improve the community with which we interact. Brothers of Delta Sigma Pi are determined professionals, and we make a difference.

Hello Everyone,

I'm absolutely thrilled to welcome to you all to the Alpha Upsilon Chapter of Delta Sigma Pi at Miami University! Delta Sigma Pi holds a special place in my heart as it has been an integral part of my college journey. It's more than just a business fraternity; it's a tight-knit community that has shaped me in profound ways.

Throughout my time with Delta Sigma Pi, I've not only found lifelong friendships but also mentors who have guided me through challenges and celebrated my successes. The memories I've made with my brothers are some of the most cherished moments of my college experience. From late-night study sessions to weekend adventures, my brothers have provided me with a supportive network and a home away from home.

If you're curious about what Delta Sigma Pi has to offer or simply want to hear some of the incredible stories and experiencesâ€” I'm here to chat. Whether it's about navigating college life, finding your place on campus, or just sharing a laugh, I'm eager to connect with you.

With Love & Honor,

Michael Ethridge

mike.ethridge@miamidsp.com
